<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="178" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d178">
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Immediate.]</seg></opener>
                            <head><persName type="from">Her Majesty’s Treasury</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">15,31027/10.</note>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Chambers,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-10-27"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 27, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen:</hi> In reply to your letter of 24th
                                instant, I am commanded by the lords commissioners of her Majesty’s
                                treasury to acquaint you that they are unable to comply with your
                                request to make a trial trip of the El Tousson, one of the iron-clad
                                vessels fitting in your yard at Birkenhead, in the course of this
                                week, or within any other suitable time.</p>
                            <p>I am, gentlemen, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>GEO. A. HAMILTON.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Messrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Laird Brothers,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead Iron Works, Birkenhead.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>